ledger-occur: Remove overlays when ledger buffer is reverted

After revert-buffer, ledger-occur-mode is disabled and
ledger-occur-current-regex is nil, but the overlays are still present, causing
the buffer to be in an inconsistent state.

ledger-time-less-p: Remove redundant function

This function is equivalent to the built-in function time-less-p, and is not
used for any other purpose.

ledger-toggle-current: Do not toggle if not in a transaction

`ledger-navigate-end-of-xact` does not work correctly if point is not in a
transaction.  We can simply explicitly check whether `ledger-thing-at-point`
returned a posting instead.

Fix #374

E.g. sort 2022/5/7 as expected.  Previously one had to write 2022/05/07 to do
the sorting reliably.  Note the zeros!

commit.message:
Use correct regexp when scanning for account names

The previous loop searched for directives, and the intention of this loop is to
search only for account names used in transactions, so we don't need to use the
combined regexp here after all.

ledger-tests-with-temp-file: Do not query when closing buffer

Mark each temp file's buffer as unmodified before attempting to kill it, so that
the user is not prompted whether they want to save it.

This makes running tests interactively through M-x ert much nicer (including
make -C test test-interactive), since the file may not be saved by the test
body.
